HEADWORD: Phillyrin
<hw>Phil"ly*rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A glucoside extracted from Phillyrea as a bitter white crystalline
substance. It is sometimes used as a febrifuge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

